name: The Mighty Ones
overview: Follow the hilarious adventures of a group of creatures: a twig, a pebble, a leaf and a strawberry. These best friends, self-named The Mighty Ones, live in an unkempt backyard belonging to a trio of equally unkempt humans whom they mistake for gods.
tagline: Break free. Live wild. Be mighty.

episodes.name: Rocksy's In a Hole Lotta Trouble
episodes.overview: When Rocksy sinks to the bottom of a giant pond, her friends must figure out how to rescue her… without Rocksy’s help.

episodes.name: The Great Invisi-Barrier
episodes.overview: When an invisible force-a-wall (a pane of glass) descends upon the yard and separates the Mighty Ones, Rocksy must figure out how to penetrate it so the group can be reunited.

episodes.name: Colossal Strawberry
episodes.overview: When Berry sees a “giant strawberry,” she’s convinced that the prophecy of the berry colossus has come true and that she’s been chosen to lead her people to their true calling. Meanwhile, Rocksy is devastated that her friend is leaving, until she realizes the strawberry is actually a piñata and Berry is in danger!

guest_stars.character: Jeff Berry / Prophetic Berry / Berry Patch (voice)
guest_stars.name: Fred Tatasciore

episodes.name: The Sappening
episodes.overview: Twig is afraid his sapping will put the Mighty Ones in peril, but Rocksy aims to show him that his sap can be used for good.

episodes.name: Wad of Friendship
episodes.overview: Berry and Rocksy are thrilled about spending every waking moment together when they get stuck to the same piece of gum, but as more people join their gum ball, things spiral out of control.

episodes.name: Twig Puts Down Roots
episodes.overview: When Twig begins to root, he thinks his dreams of becoming a Mighty Oak Tree are finally coming true! But as the Mighty Ones observe his “roots” growing in a weird and gross manner, they try to convince Twig that maybe things aren’t what they seem.

episodes.name: Egg Nag
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones accidentally knock a bird’s Egg out of its nest and must take turns trying to incubate the incredibly annoying Egg until it hatches.

episodes.name: Game On
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones move into a board game in the yard that they believe to be a “city,” and it’s all fun and games until Berry’s capitalist greed gets the best of her.

episodes.name: Creepy Caterpillar
episodes.overview: When Twig introduces Leaf to his new caterpillar friend Josh, Leaf must overcome his debilitating fear of caterpillars in order to give Josh a chance.

episodes.name: Code of Silence
episodes.overview: Hot tempered Rabbit is sick of the noise from the Mighty Ones’ games, so he makes them a bet that they can’t go for a whole day without making a sound. Desperate to see them fail, Rabbit spends the entire day making secret attempts to get the Mighty Ones to talk.

episodes.name: Bug Zapper
episodes.overview: When Mr. Ladybug finds the new bug zapper the Humans installed to be irresistible, the Mighty Ones try creating distractions to keep him from zapping himself.

episodes.name: The Helper
episodes.overview: When Rabbit realizes Rocksy is great at “conflict management,” he tricks her into helping him strong arm other yard denizens in order to get what he wants.

episodes.name: Naked Mole Wrath
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones think they are being menaced by a vicious mole rat, but it’s a case of mistaken identity.

episodes.name: Mamma Leaf
episodes.overview: Leaf discovers eggs stuck to his body and enlists Twig’s help so he can be a good momma.

episodes.name: Twig for a Day
episodes.overview: In an attempt to understand Twig better and demonstrate their appreciation for him, the Mighty Ones try to live a day as Twig. But when they end up in a precarious situation, four Twigs won’t do, and they must utilize their individual strengths in order to save themselves.

episodes.name: Eternal Day
episodes.overview: The humans in the house install a very bright light in the backyard, creating an eternal day for the Mighty Ones, who get a little loopy as a result.

episodes.name: Silly Collection
episodes.overview: Leaf has a collection of sand, but when Rocksy discovers the sand is sentient, she tries to rescue them.

episodes.name: Hat Wars
episodes.overview: Very Berry creates a new hat that everyone hates, except when Twig wears it.  Berry becomes jealous of Twig’s newly found attention and tries to steal her hat back.

guest_stars.character: Teeny Bug / Shelly / Patricia the Pear (voice)
guest_stars.name: Kari Wahlgren

episodes.name: The Queen
episodes.overview: After a group of ants steal stuff from the Mighty Ones, including Rocksy’s hair, they must head underground to the creepy ant farm in order to confront the Queen Ant to get their stuff back.

episodes.name: A Mighty Arm
episodes.overview: When the Mighty Ones accidentally neglect Twig, they make it up to him by embarking on a dangerous adventure to scale a snowman so Twig can live out of his dream of becoming the arm of the Mighty Snow Wizard… which is not actually his dream at all.

episodes.name: Two Twigs
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones can't tell the difference between Twig and a random stick bug.

episodes.name: Fresh Coat of Pain
episodes.overview: Rocksy sees fresh coat of paint spilled all over and becomes obsessed with trying to freshen up the yard.

episodes.name: A Stinky Situation
episodes.overview: Twig gets sprayed by a skunk trying to save his friends.

episodes.name: Fire-Fly
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones are cold so when they hear about a wonderful creature known as a "fire-fly," they decide it will be the answer to their problems.

episodes.name: Mr. Ladybug’s Secret
episodes.overview: When Rabbit blackmails Mr. Ladybug into doing one last job for him, Berry wants in on the action.

episodes.name: Wetyard
episodes.overview: The backyard gets flooded, so Rocksy forms a crew out of the Mighty Ones and search for dry land.

episodes.name: Bumbleberry
episodes.overview: Rocksy discovers that Verry Berry is fascinated with bees

episodes.name: Leaf’s Still Cool
episodes.overview: After reuniting with an old friend, Leaf goes to great, unsafe lengths to prove that he's still a cool daredevil.

episodes.name: Unintended Bunnyness
episodes.overview: Twig accidentally discovers Easter when he gets covered in dryer lint.

episodes.name: Berry’s Pet Threat
episodes.overview: When Berry forms a close bond with a crow that follows her around like a pet, Rocksy tries to convince Berry that it's only following her around because it's trying to eat her.

episodes.name: Shiny Leaf
episodes.overview: Leaf freaks out when he finds a blemish on his butt before a body building competition.

episodes.name: Roundy
episodes.overview: Berry gets jealous when Rocksy starts spending all of her time with a marble, and tries various attempts to make the marble "disappear."

episodes.name: The Great Grape Rescue
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones meet a courageous grape who inspires them to try to rescue his whole bunch.

episodes.name: Sneezyitis
episodes.overview: When the Mighty Ones, except for Rocksy, all mysteriously get sick at the same time, they begin to fear that they have become allergic to Rocksy.

episodes.name: Verry Berry Gets It Together
episodes.overview: When Verry Berry's adventurous spirit gets her in trouble, she joins up with a colony of army ants to learn discipline.

episodes.name: Fur Mountain
episodes.overview: Twig disappears into the coat of a dog and cohabitates with a bunch of fleas.

episodes.name: House Touchers
episodes.overview: When Rocksy is accidentally flung inside the humans' house, Berry and Twig go on a wild adventure to bring her back.

episodes.name: The Transformation
episodes.overview: Rocksy is upset when she finds out all her friends will evolve, but she will always be a pebble.

episodes.name: Ice, Ice Berry
episodes.overview: After an ice storm coats the yard in the slippery stuff, Leaf convinces the Mighty Ones that their reflections are evil doppelgangers.

episodes.name: Venomous Bush Viper
episodes.overview: When a venomous bush viper swallows Rocksy, the Mighty Ones must venture into the snake's stomach.

episodes.name: Rude-A-Snakening
episodes.overview: After being stuck inside a snake, the Mighty Ones escape, but the yard that was their home has changed.

episodes.name: Afteryard
episodes.overview: The newly renovated yard is inhospitable, but the Mighty Ones find a paradise on the refreshment table at a garden party… until the guests arrive.

episodes.name: Too Many Bens!
episodes.overview: A lack of predators in the new yard has led to an infestation of Bens, and they are looking for playmates.

episodes.name: Dance of the Machines
episodes.overview: The new humans that live in the house notice there's dirt in their yard, so they release a cleaning robot that becomes a deadly menace.

episodes.name: Fleshbeast
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones are terrorized by the human baby that runs amok through the yard, but Rocksy is drawn to its power

episodes.name: Time Leafer
episodes.overview: Everyone thinks Leaf has become loopy, but his theories about time travel might just be what the Mighty Ones need.

episodes.name: Clickety Clacks
episodes.overview: Rocksy’s “talent” goes to her head when she and Berry accidentally invent tap dancing.

episodes.name: Rocksy’s Thing
episodes.overview: Rocksy finds one end of a shoelace and tasks her friends with helping her free it so she can have a thing of her very own.

episodes.name: Twig Tat
episodes.overview: After getting advice from the Yard Tree, Twig gets a tattoo carve and keeps getting more, but ends up going too far

episodes.name: The Gnome
episodes.overview: Upon finding a giant, offensive garden gnome, the Mighty Ones debate whether to destroy it or consider it art.

episodes.name: Gherkin Returns
episodes.overview: The fifth Mighty One, Gherkin, visits for the weekend, but Berry is perplexed to discover that he has changed

episodes.name: This Blows
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones get stuck in a vortex created by a leaf blower war between neighbours.

episodes.name: Big Busyness
episodes.overview: When Leaf meets an ambitious Coffee Bean, he learns the highs and lows of business

episodes.name: Foam Party
episodes.overview: Everyone is mad at Rocksy, so she tries to make it up to them by creating fun foam to play in.

episodes.name: The Ripening
episodes.overview: Berry is invited to her family's annual celebration, which she finds tedious, but the Mighty Ones are excited to join

episodes.name: Maraca Rock
episodes.overview: Rocksy swaps lives with a maraca bead for the day.

episodes.name: The Night Pig
episodes.overview: Kensington is terrorized by her overactive imagination when a possum comes into the yard and tangles with the Mighty Ones

episodes.name: Twigula
episodes.overview: Berry mistakenly thinks that Twig is a juice sucker and tries to convince him to make her into one too.

guest_stars.character: Dad Bug / Scared Bug / Uncle Berry (voice)
guest_stars.name: Eric Bauza

episodes.name: Mystery! On the Yard Express
episodes.overview: While passengers aboard a fancy train, the Mighty Ones become part of a classic whodunit

episodes.name: Lindsay Joins the Band
episodes.overview: With an impending visit from Breht's mother, Lindsay discovers she has more fun with her next-door neighbours.

episodes.name: Battle of the Babies
episodes.overview: Rocksy's rapport with Lindsay and Breht's now feral baby inspires her friends.

episodes.name: Norman
episodes.overview: Twig and Leaf reunite with their brother Norman and compete to win his affection.

episodes.name: Party Twig
episodes.overview: Cicadas hatch and due to a misunderstanding, they anoint Twig their Party God, leaving Rocksy, Berry and Leaf in charge of keeping Twig alive.

episodes.name: Space Blasters
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones have an adventure in "space."

episodes.name: Splintered
episodes.overview: Berry gets a splinter and removing it is difficult

episodes.name: In the Pit
episodes.overview: Twig falls into a compost bin, which turns out to be a fighting pit where he must face his cowardice and fight his way out.

episodes.name: Berry's Bunker
episodes.overview: An impending threat leads Rocksy, Leaf and Twig to beg Berry to share her secret underground bunker

episodes.name: Matilda's Birthday
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones throw competing surprise parties for Matilda's birthday.

episodes.name: Clover
episodes.overview: A lucky clover offers to help Twig for a day, but once he's had a taste of good fortune, Twig has a hard time letting go

episodes.name: The Moss
episodes.overview: Leaf becomes obsessed with watching the lives of the microbes that live in Rocksy's moss.

episodes.name: Shellabyrinth
episodes.overview: Berry runs away from responsibility, only to learn her lesson and then totally disregard it because being responsible is a trap

episodes.name: Helping Hans
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones meet a multi-tool named Hans and find uses for his various attachments.

episodes.name: Twig is Dead
episodes.overview: The Mighty Ones make a statue of Twig and give him a funeral

episodes.name: Message Slab
episodes.overview: A phone falls into the yard.

episodes.name: Sacred Cup
episodes.overview: Wanting a better way to drink water, the Mighty Ones go on a quest for a cup

episodes.name: My Fair Berry
episodes.overview: Flowers invites Berry to the Bloomers Ball.

episodes.name: Pantsquest
episodes.overview: A simple brunch causes Leaf to embark on a dangerous search for cool pants

guest_stars.character: Rat King / Ben the Stinkbug / Dad Bug (voice)
guest_stars.name: Eric Bauza

guest_stars.character: Carder / MC Thorax / Günter / Ricky Buzz / Dave (voice)
guest_stars.name: Tru Valentino

episodes.name: Berry's Brain
episodes.overview: Twig is the only one who knows that Berry's brain is being eaten by a parasitic worm that is making her act nicer than usual.

episodes.name: Chompers for Cobcorn
episodes.overview: Bernard steals Rabbit's teeth, and when Berry gets mistaken as an accomplice, they go on the run together

episodes.name: Boat Day
episodes.overview: Berry's head grows to a monstrous size and keeps growing.
